{
  "texts": [
    "Classes end 10 minutes before the end of the second hour so that students can attend a different class if their options dictate that two classes occur contiguously on their timetable.",
    "Work produced in class is discussed further in the Virtual Learning Environment (VLE) between the tutor and students.",
    "Table 1 offers an overview of themes and practicums in the module together with the primary creative skill associated with each theme.",
    "It is important to highlight that the entire module is intended as a way to develop the Originality/creativity skill (Sawyer, 2012, p. 55).",
    "The last two classes are focused on evaluating their own production as well as the production of others."
  ]
}